[OzMoz - Operating System]

dependencies:
- Kernel
- Net
- VGA
- Sound
- Bootloader 
- Terminal 
- TextEdit "0_Dit"



-> Ring 0 operations
-> FullHD Support 
-> Terminal Only (Screen splitting enabled)
-> runnable on modern processor platforms (x64 13th gen w/all instructions)


steps:

write bootloader in c and asm 
    -> boot from disk (a:)
    -> write bootloader to HDD / Boot Sector       
    -> bootloader should hook and run kernel from Kernel/run.c
    -> kernel operates and builds system dependencies (vga/sound/net)
    -> kernel boots up terminal for user interaction

commands:

ls
md
rm
cp
mv
ned

